Lagos – The Nigeria Football Federation (NFF) has been given more time to make recommendation for the position of the Super Eagles Technical Adviser job. This was the highlight of the meeting between the Ministy of Youth and Sports Development and the NFF, which our correspondent gathered went very well with both bodies agreeing to work together in the interest of Nigerian football. “NFF will take the next few days to conduct further interviews with the prospective coaches/candidates seeking to become the Super Eagles Technical Adviser. -Advertisement- “Thereafter NFF will meet with the Ministry to reach a final decision on the matter and come out with the name of the new Technical Adviser,” we learnt. In a related development, Key Performance Indicators, (KPIs) are to be fully worked out and put in place before a new national coach is hired. Meanwhile, the Ministry has also tasked the NFF on absolute commitment to the rebuilding process for Nigerian football and the national teams in all areas. Recalled that Gernot Rohr was named as the Super Eagles Technical Adviser in 2016 and he was the longest-serving coach of the team with his over five years in charge. He was sacked in December 2021 while still being owed several months’ salaries as well as bonuses and allowances.